pinguicula alpina is a carnivorous plant that is distributed from the alpine and pyrneese mountains of europe on to the himalayas of asia(north india,nepal and tibet).
pinguicula alpina is one of the most common of the genus pinguicula(along whith p.vulgaris).
its flowers are white spotted whith a yellow center,its insect trapping leaves come in various colours:yellow-green,green-orange and even red.